      <item>
        <title>Whonix-Gateway 16.0.2.7 Can&#39;t boot into CLI</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[HulaHoop]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>The console viewer works OK with Whonix cli. The RAM problem is caused by XFCE moving from lightdm to gdm3 in Bullseye and that’s why it ignores rads.</p>
<p>We need to find some way to configure gdm3 to work with 512MB to fix this.</p>
